{"body": "Making `Module#define_method` public would help the code read a bit more clearly. \r\n\r\nThat said, I think it's better still to treat the Module (`@mixin`) as an object with its own encapsulation. In this case, its responsibility is to define methods according to certain params (ie., `Association::Builder#define_*`).\r\n\r\nIn any case, a win for ActiveRecord.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/2757166", "created_at": "2011-11-16T08:46:57Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/3636#issuecomment-2757166", "updated_at": "2011-11-16T08:46:57Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 3636, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/emmanuel/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/emmanuel/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/emmanuel/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/emmanuel", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/emmanuel/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/emmanuel", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/emmanuel/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/83611ed7f7ed587603fbdffc691ea989?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F82674fc29bc0d9895cee346548c2cb5c.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/emmanuel/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/emmanuel/received_events", "gravatar_id": "83611ed7f7ed587603fbdffc691ea989", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/emmanuel/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "emmanuel", "type": "User", "id": 7657, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/emmanuel/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523f5c6ebd354364b9017436"}, "id": 2757166, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/3636"}
